---
const features = [
  {
    title: 'Write the tool. Skip the boilerplate.',
    body: 'You write a `defineTool({ input, output, handler })`. We handle the JSON-RPC, the schema validation, the tools/list contract, the auth header, the timeouts.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Schemas you write once',
    body: 'Define a Zod schema and you get the runtime check, the JSON Schema the agent reads, and the TypeScript types — all from the same line.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Auth, rate limits and timeouts ship in',
    body: 'Bearer or API-key auth at the server, per-tool rate limits, deadline-aware timeouts. All composable. None to install separately.',
  },
  {
    title: 'See every tool call live',
    body: '`mcify dev` opens an inspector with a real-time call log, a playground to invoke tools by hand, and a chat tab that talks to Claude or GPT directly.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Your AI assistant already knows the rules',
    body: 'Every project ships an AGENTS.md that Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf and Copilot Workspace read automatically. New tools land in the same shape every time.',
  },
  {
    title: 'One command to ship to any cloud',
    body: '`mcify deploy cloudflare` / `vercel` / `fly` / `railway` / `docker`. Same handler everywhere. The CLI generates the config and calls the platform CLI for you.',
  },
];
---

<section class="section border-t border-ink-800/80">
  <div class="container-wide">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="section-title">What you actually get</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">Six things you'd build by hand the first week. Already in the box.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {features.map((f) => (
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-base font-semibold tracking-tight">{f.title}</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-400" set:html={f.body.replaceAll(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code class="rounded bg-ink-800/60 px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] text-ink-200">$1</code>')}></p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
